rmat-external-drives-on-iphone-and-ipad.jpg\"/\u003e\n    \u003c/picture\u003e\n                                        \u003cfigcaption\u003eYash Wate / MakeUseOf\u003c/figcaption\u003e\n                        \n    \u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n    \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\n            \n                \n    \n    \n        \n    \n\n    \n            \u003c/header\u003e\n\n                                                        \n        \n\n        \n                                        \n                                \n            \n                        \n        \n        \n\n    \n            \n    \n                                                            \n            \n    \n    \n                                                                            \n                                \n                                \n                                                \n            \n        \n    \n        \n                                                                                                                                                                    \n                \n    \n    \n        \n    \n\n    \n    \n            \n    \n    \n            \n                                                    \n                        \n    \n                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n        \n    \n        \n                                                                                                                                                                    \n                \n    \n    \n        \n    \n\n    \n    \n            \n    \n    \n            \n    \n    \n                                                        \n                                \n                                \n                                                \n            \n        \n    \n        \n                                                                                                                                                                    \n                \n    \n    \n        \n    \n\n    \n    \n            \n    \n    \n            \n    \n    \n    \n        \n    \n        \n                                                                                                                                                                    \n                \n    \n    \n        \n    \n\n    \n    \n            \n    \n    \n            \n    \n    \n                                                        \n                                \n                                \n                                                \n            \n        \n    \n        \n                                                                                                                                                                    \n                \n    \n    \n        \n    \n\n    \n    \n            \n    \n    \n            \n    \n    \n                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n        \n    \n        \n                                                                                                                                                                    \n                \n    \n    \n        \n    \n\n    \n    \n            \n    \n    \n            \n    \n    \n                                                        \n                                \n                                \n                                                \n            \n        \n    \n        \n                                                                                                                                                                    \n                \n    \n    \n        \n    \n\n    \n    \n            \n    \n    \n            \n    \n    \n    \n        \n    \n        \n                                                                                                                                                                    \n                \n    \n    \n        \n    \n\n    \n    \n            \n    \n    \n            \n    \n    \n                                                        \n                                \n                                \n                                                \n            \n        \n    \n        \n                                                                                                                                                                    \n            \n    \n    \n        \n                    \n                        \n                                    \n\n\n\n\u003cdiv id=\"article-body\" itemprop=\"articleBody\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eFormatting external drives has never been possible on an iPhone or iPad. However, this changes with iOS 18 and iPadOS 18, which introduce the ability to erase and format external drives using your iPhone or iPad. I\u0026#39;ll show you how to use this feature.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"using-the-files-app-to-format-drives-on-your-iphone-or-ipad\"\u003e Using the Files App to Format Drives on Your iPhone or iPad \u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eApple has added a new Erase feature to \u003ca href=\"http://www.makeuseof.com/tag/use-ios-files-app-iphone-ipad/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003ethe built-in Files app\u003c/a\u003e. It\u0026#39;s pretty to use, and all you need is an adapter or a USB hub, depending on your iPhone or iPad model and preference. Here\u0026#39;s what you need to do to format an external drive:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\u003col\u003e\u003cli\u003e Plug in the external drive you want to format using an adapter or a USB hub. \u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e Open the \u003cstrong\u003eFiles\u003c/strong\u003e app, and you\u0026#39;ll see the drive name under \u003cstrong\u003eLocations\u003c/strong\u003e in the left sidebar. \u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e Tap and hold the drive and select \u003cstrong\u003eErase\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/how-to-format-external-drives-on-iphone-ipad-1.jpg\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/how-to-format-external-drives-on-iphone-ipad-1.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/how-to-format-external-drives-on-iphone-ipad-1.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/how-to-format-external-drives-on-iphone-ipad-1.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/how-to-format-external-drives-on-iphone-ipad-1.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/how-to-format-external-drives-on-iphone-ipad-1.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/how-to-format-external-drives-on-iphone-ipad-1.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/how-to-format-external-drives-on-iphone-ipad-1.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/how-to-format-external-drives-on-iphone-ipad-1.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003cimg width=\"2388\" height=\"1668\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"Erase option in the context menu for an external driver in the Files app on an iPad.\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/how-to-format-external-drives-on-iphone-ipad-1.jpg\" src=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/how-to-format-external-drives-on-iphone-ipad-1.jpg\"/\u003e \u003c/picture\u003e \u003c/figure\u003e \u003c/div\u003e \u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e According to your requirements, choose an appropriate format for the drive between \u003cstrong\u003eAPFS\u003c/strong\u003e, \u003cstrong\u003eExFAT\u003c/strong\u003e, and \u003cstrong\u003eMS-DOS (FAT)\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/how-to-format-external-drives-on-iphone-ipad-2.jpg\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/how-to-format-external-drives-on-iphone-ipad-2.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/how-to-format-external-drives-on-iphone-ipad-2.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/how-to-format-external-drives-on-iphone-ipad-2.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/how-to-format-external-drives-on-iphone-ipad-2.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/how-to-format-external-drives-on-iphone-ipad-2.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/how-to-format-external-drives-on-iphone-ipad-2.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/how-to-format-external-drives-on-iphone-ipad-2.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/how-to-format-external-drives-on-iphone-ipad-2.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003cimg width=\"2388\" height=\"1668\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"Choosing the file system format for external drive in the Files app.\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/how-to-format-external-drives-on-iphone-ipad-2.jpg\" src=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/how-to-format-external-drives-on-iphone-ipad-2.jpg\"/\u003e \u003c/picture\u003e \u003c/figure\u003e \u003c/div\u003e \u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e If you want to rename the drive, tap the \u003cstrong\u003eNAME\u003c/strong\u003e text field at the top and type a new name. \u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e Finally, hit \u003cstrong\u003eErase\u003c/strong\u003e in the top-right corner and tap \u003cstrong\u003eErase\u003c/strong\u003e in the confirmation prompt to begin erasing and formatting the drive.\u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/how-to-format-external-drives-on-iphone-ipad-3.jpg\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/how-to-format-external-drives-on-iphone-ipad-3.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/how-to-format-external-drives-on-iphone-ipad-3.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/how-to-format-external-drives-on-iphone-ipad-3.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/how-to-format-external-drives-on-iphone-ipad-3.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/how-to-format-external-drives-on-iphone-ipad-3.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/how-to-format-external-drives-on-iphone-ipad-3.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/how-to-format-external-drives-on-iphone-ipad-3.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/how-to-format-external-drives-on-iphone-ipad-3.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003cimg width=\"2388\" height=\"1668\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"Confirmation prompt asking to confirm erasing and formatting external drive.\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/how-to-format-external-drives-on-iphone-ipad-3.jpg\" src=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/how-to-format-external-drives-on-iphone-ipad-3.jpg\"/\u003e \u003c/picture\u003e \u003c/figure\u003e \u003c/div\u003e \u003c/li\u003e \u003c/ol\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eYou\u0026#39;ll now see a loading icon next to the drive, indicating the formatting is underway. Once finished, it\u0026#39;ll turn into a checkmark. You can then proceed to access and use the drive. When you\u0026#39;re done, simply unplug it from your iPhone or iPad.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"choosing-the-correct-format-for-your-external-drive\"\u003e Choosing the Correct Format for Your External Drive \u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eChoosing \u003ca href=\"https://www.makeuseof.com/tag/mac-file-system-external-drive/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003ethe correct file system for your external drive\u003c/a\u003e is crucial and boils down to what devices you plan to use it with. Here\u0026#39;s a quick rundown to help you decide:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAPFS (Apple File System):\u003c/strong\u003e Apple\u0026#39;s proprietary file system, APFS, is ideal if you want to use the drive exclusively with Apple devices, like an iPhone, iPad, Mac, or Apple TV. Additional options like \u003cstrong\u003eCase Sensitive\u003c/strong\u003e and \u003cstrong\u003eEncrypted\u003c/strong\u003e are available with this format. While the latter secures data on the drive, the former treats uppercase and lowercase letters in file names differently to avoid naming conflicts. \u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eExFAT:\u003c/strong\u003e This is a great choice if you want the freedom to use the drive or SD card on various devices, including Apple devices, Windows and Linux computers, TVs, Android phones, and digital cameras. \u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMS-DOS (FAT):\u003c/strong\u003e It offers great compatibility with older systems. However, it\u0026#39;s a relatively older format and ideal only for smaller storage needs due to its 4GB file size limit. \u003c/li\u003e \u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eHaving the ability to format drives in the Files app is incredibly useful and eliminates the need for a Mac or PC. However, that\u0026#39;s not all the built-in file manager in iOS and iPadOS is capable of. Thanks to recent iOS and iPadOS updates, \u003ca href=\"https://www.makeuseof.com/what-you-can-do-with-files-app-on-iphone/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eyou can perform various other tasks with the Files app on an iPhone or iPad\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\n    \n        \n\n    \n\n        \n\n\n                \n        \n        \n\n\n        \n\n\n\n\n\n                    \n        \n    \u003c/article\u003e\n\n    \n        \u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
